<!doctype html public "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN//2.0">
<html><head>
<title>Install Agent</title>
<link rev="made" href="mailto:wolff@crc.ricoh.com">
</head><body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#c40026" vlink="#e40026">

<set entity name=title>Install Agent</set>
<!-- read interform file="heading.inc" process -->

<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><th width=340 align=left>Ricoh Silicon Valley<td> PIA<br>
<tr><th width=340 align=right><a href="home">&agentName;</a>:
    <td>Install Agent<br>
</table>
(heading simplified to save time during startup)
<p>
<hr>
<set entity name="name"><if><get name=urlQuery>
    <then><agent-install>&urlQuery;</agent-install></then></if></set>

<if><get entity name="name">
<then>
  <set entity name=type><get form name=type></set>
  <h2>&name; installed:</h2> <p>
  <table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
  <tr><th width=340><td><br>
  <tr><th align=right>&name;:
  <tr><th width=340><td> <a href="/&name;">home page</a>
  <tr><th width=340><td> <a href="/&name;/">index</a>
  <if><test not exact match="&name;">&type;</test>
    <then>
    <tr><th width=340><td> <a href="/&type;">/&type;</a> (type agent)
    <tr><th width=340><td> <a href="/&type;/&name;">/&type;/&name;</a>
    </then>
  </if>
  <tr><th width=340><td> <a href="/&name;/options">options</a>
  <tr><th width=340><td> <form action="/Agency/remove_agent" method="POST">
	 <input name="agent" value="&name;" type=hidden>
	 <input type="submit" value="Remove &name;">
	 </form>
  </ul>
  </table>
  <hr>
  Query string: <code>&urlQuery;</code>

</then>
<else>
<h2> Form for installing an agent</h2>
<form action="/Agency/install_agent" method="POST">
<input type="submit" value="Install">
Name:<input name="agent" value="agent_name" size=30>
Type:<input name="type" value="">
</form>

You can usually leave the <em>type</em> blank and it will default to the name.
If a class-declaration module <code>PIA::Agent::<em>Type</em></code> exists,
it will be loaded if necessary.  The standard ones are in <code><a
href="/PIA/src/lib/perl/PIA/Agent/">/PIA/src/lib/perl/PIA/Agent/</a></code><p>

</else>
</if>

 Query string: <code>&urlQuery;</code>
  
  
<hr>
<b>URL:</b> &lt;<a href="&url;">&url;</a>&gt;<br>
<b>Source:</b> <a href="/PIA/src/Agents/&agentName;/&fileName;">&fileName;</a>
<b>File:</b> <a href="file:&filePath;">&filePath;</a>
<hr>
<a href="/">PIA</a> || <a href="/Agency">Agency</a>:
<a href="&agentName;/">index</a>
<a href="&agentName;/options">options</a>
